cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.IR 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for recognition and classification of animals in camera trap images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the generalization of algorithms to new environments, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of algorithms for security purposes, which could fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses the use of image retrieval techniques, which could fall under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
